Benin- A Chieftain of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) and former candidate of Oredo Federal constituency, Omo Osagie Efosa has enjoined Christian faithful in Edo State and Nigeria in general to be tolerant and abide to the virtues of the peaceful disposition of Jesus Christ whose birth the entire world had just celebrated. Omo Osagie, also known as the Mighty man, who spoke to journalists in Benin, noted that this year’s celebration came at a time when the world was and still combatting the resurgence of the Coronavirus pandemic, which has forced many countries to ramp up health safety protocols at a time when people traditionally gather to share love in celebration of the birth of Jesus Christ. He also said that besides the global health emergency of COVID-19, Nigeria still faces security and economic challenges which, he expressed optimism that sooner or later Nigeria will come out of it and Oredo people would have cause to smile once again. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He, however, praised God and expressed happiness that the resilience and positive attitudes of Nigerians did not stop the country from prevailing against the challenges but also ensured that their strains did not stop a hitch free and responsible celebration of Christmas, just as they look forward to a peaceful celebration of the new year in the state and Nigeria at large. The former house of representatives candidate also thanked the people of faith for remembering Oredo local government and by extension Edo state in their prayers during the yuletide, especially for divine guidance for the government in its efforts to improve security and strengthen the economy of the state in the new year. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION